content: Since today is April 1, the Fools Day,
I must choose the topic of my loss game :))
because my loss means, I was the Fool :)
some weeks ago, there was the renju tournament in Finland, Tampere.
Timo got 6 points from 7, me too,
but I got 2nd place, with worse coefficient.
My only loss game was to Andry Purk.
And today we will analyse that game.
First, I was fooled by an opening ;)
I was soooo sure he would open d11.
But I almost fainted when I saw d3.
why must D11?D3 was also popular
Because until then d11 had been his favotite
But recently, he has more passion to new ideas.
How many of you have every played it?
well I've been white here once
I played this five when I used white
I played it as white long ago...
this 5th black is very hard to play,I think
Yes, white should be better here,
but it requires some knowledge or skill.
I had played some games with this 7th moves before, each time as white, if I remember right :)
Of course, mistakes can also happen,
besides, until now I am not sure if this 10th is best or not.
and later on I did not think of other possible 10th.
If you were white now, where would you put thr 10th move?
wow, i8 and j9 - two concepts.
Indeed, if white goes i8, black will go j9.
So we have to compare the outcomes of these 2 variants.
Since the game had only 50 minutes time, without extra-time,
so I did not want to get into complications, so I didnt use four.
I thought, if I play four and I do not win, I will be surrounded.
So I wanted him to take j9 point instead.
For a moment, lets imagine, if white takes j9, what will happen.
i will choose one "up" supporter, and later one "down" supporter
and test the variant a little
can try softly on left side
so we saw, black cannot win in upper area.
therefore its better to stop here
maybe some other 18th move is better for white
you can develop softly on left side
f7 is nice point, i agree with you
Samsone, do you want to try f7, or you have other ideas?
maybe white can attack more bravely here
is it not the best for white?
if black tries vcf, will face cut
who wants to show white win now
no matter win or fail, its only a study room anyway
slappanu, Yue, xuwu, benben, Samsone, yuelee00, tommy, shuwang, soujun, jinzhiyuye, dongfujia, bergamot, charles, bendan, out.
I am thinking and comes the CHECK~ HOHO
let the one who is putting stones, play all the way
I was looking for the,,but this seems more simple
only guest cannot play moves, others can :)
dear guest134, next Saturday, make student ID for self, and enjoy class with us
or today, we can say this way:
maybe i find vct ,but i am not sure
now i am fool again, must change
i think it is too complicated
was there also a shorter win?
lets admire this win for 20 seconds
Samsone, yuelee00, Yue, tommy, slappanu, shuwang, charles, dongfujia, bendan, soujun, benben, out, bergamot, Asuka.
maybe white can attack directly g6 e8
i have no idea about this
yes, if all straight attacks fail,
In my game, I did not use the four.
And so we played like this.
The next move was natural too.
if black wants to fight in this game,
he has to stop whites from moving to left area.
He risked, and gave me space for quite straight attack.
And now, I spent most of my time on thinking about white attack.
The main idea was to give pressure on 3x3 point at h11.
I don't know if this plan was good or not.
Then he played to h11, to kill the 3x3 threat.
But he had to risk, and not let whites develop in lower area.
I had very little time left by then. :)
In order to get white attack on left side,
i needed a stone to h14,
then i could also take f9, and put vcf threat to f10.
and now, white could make a vcf threat to d10 or c10.
but, i was not sure of one thing: does black have own vcf threat if i go there, or not.
I spent 3 minutes just to check his vcf
After 3 minutes, I was sure, he had no vcf.
and when I had 1 minute left,
Yes, black can play many fours, but no win.
it was very difficult to count all this
so thats why i wasted my precious 3 minutes
to make sure black cannot win here by vcf, if i do this 38.
in real tournament, you can only use your head
Andry did not even try to use fours now.
According to his words, he too had realized than black doesnt win by VCF. ;)
i had less than a minute.
Now, it was almost crazy situation.
and black has so many fours!
Above all, I was afraid he might have VCF.
he started to use fours now.
but because of stone 50 together with 60 and 24 create horizontal cut,
and then, i had about 30 seconds, he had a bit over a minute, i think.
he stopped from here, when he saw i don't have vcf any more.
assuming its a good way to get tempo,
since i dont have vcf below
and because i had 20 seconds left,
i was unable to notice all details already.
I had totally forgotten about my four at h14.
i could push it to overline.
In fact, the correct play for him would have been:
but well, we both made poor moves in time trouble.
He has 3 move win, from m7,
but he didnt even look there :))
so i got a chance to survive for a while
So I knew I can spend 1 second per move
so i had to push attacking immediately.
it is a nice game indeed
Today's analysis let me realize, maybe four at j9 would be better for white.
Anyway, it was an exciting game.
Later I analysed, another 38 would be better.
Still white vcf and black doesnt have vcf.
then maybe i would have better chances for attack.
So, this was the analusis of Fool Ando's game :) thank you all for participating, you did a good job! Nice Team Analysis!
